items.title: The stock market rarely scores hat tricks. This strategist fears what’s next.
items.description: The S&P 500 has managed two consecutive 20%-plus years in a row, but that has rarely led to a third great year, says this strategist.

items.title: I’m the executor of my 90-year-old aunt’s estate. A neighbor threatened me and wants to buy her house. What should I do?
items.description: “I believe she doesn’t have that much time left.”

items.title: ‘He ended up homeless and penniless’: My uncle conned my father into signing over their mother’s house. What can I do?
items.description: “His brother went to the prison where my dad was incarcerated and had him sign over the house.”

items.title: These are the most popular Moneyist columns of 2024
items.description: Divorce, student debt, airline travel, house purchase and inheritance comprised the top 5 most read columns of the year.

items.title: Stock Futures Rise to Start New Year
items.description: Technology stocks were leading gains in premarket trading, with chip stocks and cryptocurrency-linked names rising.
